						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in a garden near the Āḷvārcheruvu Tank.</p>						

						<p>Ś. 1326: 1404 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of date given, viz., Śaka 1326, Tāraṇa, Mārgaḻi, 21, correspond to 1404-A.D., December 18, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>This inscription registers an undertaking given by the <hi rend="italic">sthānattār</hi> in Tirumalai to Giridēvappa, brother of ŚAntappa NAgabhadran<note n="116-1">The name is given as NAgapaṇṇan in the T.T.D, Text.</note>and son of SAyaṇṇa, for celebrating the 7th day festival in the LakshmInārasimhaṉ <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">tiruvōlakkachchiṟappu</hi> during the summer festival in lieu of having received 600 <hi rend="italic">paṇam.</hi></p>						

						<p>Text published in Tirumalai Tirupati Dēvasthānam Epigraphical series Vol. I, No. 191.</p>						

						</summary>
